summary:
sporesman
 replied to your post  “have you read the books killing eve was based on?? are they good”
                    
       ...
body:
sporesman replied to your post “have you read the books killing eve was based on?? are they good”
the show is better, villanelle was way more sexualized in the book and eve was more insecure

leritzcrackaires replied to your post

I think the book is fantastic and it’s really incredibly entertaining to link the differences and similarities between the book and the TV series. The book isn’t remotely dull, it’s very informative in terms of Villanelle’s early life and details regarding the link between MI5/MI6/The Twelve. Definitely recommend!!

musingsofauniversedisturber replied to your post

The book is good, but in my opinion the show is better!

summary: When supposedly "Russian" characters played by Western actors speak "Russian" on TV and the pronunciation is roughly right but...
body:
When supposedly “Russian” characters played by Western actors speak “Russian” on TV and the pronunciation is roughly right but the inflections are all wrong? like if you agree

It’s like those terrible automated voice systems, except worse, since those are actually designed to not sound terrible when the words are strung together in random ways. Hell, I’d prefer nails over chalkboard.
